%%
%% How to generate figure-captions of the form section-figure of section ?
%%
%% First is to use a new counter which depends on section. looks like that
%%   \newcounter{sectionfigure}[section]
%% and renew the \thefigure counter
%%   \renewcommand{\thefigure}{\thesection.\thesectionfigure}
%% This solution needs to update the counter by adding
%%   \refstepcounter{sectionfigure}
%% before every \caption inside figures. Ugly but works very fine
%%
%% Second, and much more clever,  solution is to add
   \makeatletter
       \@addtoreset{figure}{chapter}
       \@addtoreset{table}{chapter}  % were doing it for tables as well
   \makeatother
%% into the praeamble and to
   \renewcommand{\thefigure}{\thechapter.\arabic{figure}}
   \renewcommand{\thetable}{\thechapter.\arabic{table}}
%% renew the \thefigure-counter. Quick and much more convenient !  ;-)


